Based on the explanations on
https://robertheaton.com/2013/07/29/padding-oracle-attack/
and examining the decryption scheme, I've modified my solution to the 3rd lab
to take into account the online checking of the ciphertext and the plaintext
feedback.

Brute-forcing every byte of the message blocks gave me the flag:
CRYPTO_CTF{FrunzaVerdeFoiDeFicusAlgoritmulNuESigur}
